{"data":{},"content":"<h1 id=\"brightjs\">BrightJs</h1><p>A tiny library for small webpages.</p>\n<div class=\"admonition admonition-info\">\n    <p class=\"admonition-title\">Note</p>\n    <p>You should consider not using it, since I will not bring any further update to it.</p>\n\n    </div><h2 id=\"use-it\">Use it</h2><p>The minified version is available <a target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://raw.githubusercontent.com/bright-js/bright-js.github.io/main/public/bright.min.js\" title=\"null\">here</a>.</p>\n<h1 id=\"docs\">Docs</h1><h2 id=\"select-an-htmlelement\">Select an HTMLElement</h2><pre><code class=\"hljs\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\">const</span> elem = $(<span class=\"hljs-string\">&#x27;h1&#x27;</span>);</code></pre><h2 id=\"access-it-39-s-content-and-modify-it\">Access it&#39;s content and modify it.</h2><pre><code class=\"hljs\"><span class=\"hljs-comment\">// Change it&#x27;s HTML</span>\n$(<span class=\"hljs-string\">&#x27;h1&#x27;</span>).<span class=\"hljs-title function_\">html</span>(<span class=\"hljs-string\">&#x27;Hello world!&#x27;</span>);\n\n<span class=\"hljs-comment\">// access to it&#x27;s HTML</span>\n<span class=\"hljs-keyword\">const</span> html = $(<span class=\"hljs-string\">&#x27;h1&#x27;</span>).<span class=\"hljs-title function_\">html</span>();<span class=\"hljs-comment\">// =&gt; &#x27;Hello world!&#x27;</span>\n\n<span class=\"hljs-comment\">// change it&#x27;s content</span>\n$(<span class=\"hljs-string\">&#x27;h1&#x27;</span>).<span class=\"hljs-title function_\">text</span>(<span class=\"hljs-string\">&#x27;Hello world! &gt;:)&#x27;</span>);\n\n<span class=\"hljs-comment\">// access to it&#x27;s content</span>\n<span class=\"hljs-keyword\">const</span> text = $(<span class=\"hljs-string\">&#x27;h1&#x27;</span>).<span class=\"hljs-title function_\">text</span>();<span class=\"hljs-comment\">// =&gt; &#x27;Hello world! &gt;:)&#x27;</span></code></pre><p><strong>Note:</strong> if you select many different tags, it will returns an array </p>\n<pre><code class=\"hljs\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\">var</span> text = $(<span class=\"hljs-string\">&#x27;h1&#x27;</span>).<span class=\"hljs-title function_\">text</span>();\n<span class=\"hljs-comment\">// =&gt; [&#x27;Hello world!&#x27;, ...]</span></code></pre><h2 id=\"use-it-with-an-object\">Use it with an object</h2><pre><code class=\"hljs\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\">const</span> tag = <span class=\"hljs-variable language_\">document</span>.<span class=\"hljs-title function_\">getElementById</span>(<span class=\"hljs-string\">&#x27;myId&#x27;</span>);\n<span class=\"hljs-keyword\">const</span> elem = $(tag);</code></pre><h2 id=\"add-an-event-listener\">Add an event listener</h2><pre><code class=\"hljs\">$(<span class=\"hljs-string\">&#x27;h1&#x27;</span>).<span class=\"hljs-title function_\">on</span>(<span class=\"hljs-string\">&#x27;click&#x27;</span>, <span class=\"hljs-function\">(<span class=\"hljs-params\">event</span>) =&gt;</span> {\n    $.<span class=\"hljs-title function_\">log</span>(<span class=\"hljs-string\">&#x27;Clicked!&#x27;</span>);\n});\n$(<span class=\"hljs-variable language_\">window</span>).<span class=\"hljs-title function_\">on</span>(<span class=\"hljs-string\">&#x27;load&#x27;</span>, <span class=\"hljs-function\">() =&gt;</span> {\n    $.<span class=\"hljs-title function_\">log</span>(<span class=\"hljs-string\">&#x27;Loaded!&#x27;</span>);\n});</code></pre><h2 id=\"load-external-html-in-a-tag\">Load external html in a tag</h2><pre><code class=\"hljs\">$(<span class=\"hljs-string\">&#x27;myDiv&#x27;</span>)\n    .<span class=\"hljs-title function_\">load</span>(<span class=\"hljs-string\">&#x27;/path/to/file.html&#x27;</span>)\n    <span class=\"hljs-comment\">// you can execute a function when the content is loaded</span>\n    .<span class=\"hljs-title function_\">then</span>(<span class=\"hljs-function\">() =&gt;</span> {\n        $.<span class=\"hljs-title function_\">log</span>(<span class=\"hljs-string\">&#x27;Loaded!&#x27;</span>);\n    });</code></pre><h2 id=\"change-some-css\">Change some css</h2><pre><code class=\"hljs\">$(<span class=\"hljs-string\">&#x27;h1&#x27;</span>)\n    <span class=\"hljs-comment\">// change it&#x27;s style by providing a property and a value</span>\n    .<span class=\"hljs-title function_\">css</span>(<span class=\"hljs-string\">&#x27;color&#x27;</span>, <span class=\"hljs-string\">&#x27;red&#x27;</span>)\n    \n    <span class=\"hljs-comment\">// you can also do it with an object</span>\n    .<span class=\"hljs-title function_\">css</span>({\n        <span class=\"hljs-attr\">color</span>: <span class=\"hljs-string\">&#x27;red&#x27;</span>,\n        <span class=\"hljs-attr\">fontWeight</span>: <span class=\"hljs-string\">&#x27;bolder&#x27;</span>\n    });\n    \n<span class=\"hljs-comment\">// access to a property</span>\n$.<span class=\"hljs-title function_\">log</span>($(<span class=\"hljs-string\">&#x27;h1&#x27;</span>).<span class=\"hljs-title function_\">css</span>(<span class=\"hljs-string\">&#x27;color&#x27;</span>));<span class=\"hljs-comment\">// =&gt; &#x27;red&#x27;</span>\n\n<span class=\"hljs-comment\">// or</span>\n$.<span class=\"hljs-title function_\">log</span>($(<span class=\"hljs-string\">&#x27;h1&#x27;</span>).<span class=\"hljs-title function_\">css</span>(<span class=\"hljs-string\">&#x27;color&#x27;</span>));<span class=\"hljs-comment\">// =&gt; &#x27;rgb(255, 0, 0)&#x27;</span></code></pre>","label":"Introduction"}